The paper discusses privacy mechanisms and their guarantees, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of noise parameters, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the security of thresholding schemes, which is related to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the use of definitions to capture different attacker models, which is related to information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper discusses the implications of these definitions on the security of data, which is related to databases (cs.DB).
